{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Others provided AI educational experience without stating the assessment method (Ho et al., 2019; Lee et al., 2020; Tseng et al., 2021).",
    "Heinze et al. (2010) conducted AI learning activities without assessing learning outcomes.",
    "Shamir and Levin (2022) designed a questionnaire based on \"constructionist validated robotics learning\" for machine learning construction (the questionnaire included statements such as \"I can make a ML system\", \"I can propose ideas for using ML to solve problems.\").",
    "Dai et al. (2023) used multiple choice questions (e.g., \"Which of the following devices or systems is an intelligent agent?\")",
    "to evaluate the AI knowledge of primary school students according to Bloom's Taxonomy."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Others provided AI educational experience without stating the assessment method (Ho et al., 2019; Lee et al., 2020; Tseng et al., 2021).",
    "Heinze et al. (2010) conducted AI learning activities without assessing learning outcomes.",
    "Shamir and Levin (2022) designed a questionnaire based on \"constructionist validated robotics learning\" for machine learning construction (the questionnaire included statements such as \"I can make a ML system\", \"I can propose ideas for using ML to solve problems.\").",
    "Dai et al. (2023) used multiple choice questions (e.g., \"Which of the following devices or systems is an intelligent agent?\")"
  ]
}